article.headline: Central Michigan 85, UMKC 68
article.story: MOUNT PLEASANT, Mich. (AP) -- Jordan Bitzer scored 14 of his 17 points in the second half to help Central Michigan overcome a 16-point halftime deficit and beat Missouri-Kansas City 85-68 on Sunday. The freshman guard gave the Chippewas (2-1) their first lead of the game on a 3-pointer that made it 47-46. UMKC (2-1) briefly took back the lead, but a 3-pointer by Chris Kellermann put Central Michigan up 53-51, and the Chippewas would never look back. Dane Brumagin led UMKC with 26 points, and Dominique Johnson added 14. Brumagin scored 19 of his points as the Kangaroos built a 20-point lead late in the first half. But Bitzer and Kellermann started the second with back-to-back 3-pointers, and the Chippewas went on a 21-4 run. Central Michigan pushed the lead to as many as 21 points late in the second half. The Kangaroos were outscored 59-26 in the period and were 1-of-11 on 3-pointers after making six in the first half. Giordan Watson scored 17 points for the Chippewas, all after halftime.
